      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.XK3M0StmPA3blYw1]{Feat Boosts}</p>\n<p>When you use Shot on the Run, you can select two targets to attack during your movement instead of one. Both attacks take a –4 penalty. All restrictions of Shot on the Run apply to both targets, and your movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity from either target. You can’t target the same creature twice with this ability. You must be at least 7th level to select this feat boost.</p>"
